            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.18.7" />
                <note type="curatorial">230 House Collection</note>
                <fw type="curatorial">7</fw>
                
                
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                EDITORIAL DEPARTMENT            ST. LOUIS POST-DISPATCH</fw>
                <opener><dateline>May 14, 1936
                ST. LOUIS, MO.</dateline> 
                
                
                <salute>Dear Comrade:</salute>
                </opener>
                
                <p>Enclosed find proof. Another book on Hitler has just arrived, and I am sending it to you. Please combine these two in one review, and give evaluation of the books at the end.</p>
                
                <p>It's too bad to bother you, but it seems necessary.</p>
                
                <p>The new article should not be over 450 words.</p>
                
                <p>In using the historical present, be sure to make it clear that you are not referring to our moment. There are a lot of doughheads!</p>
                
                <p>Later I'll send you a good novel.</p>
                
                <p>Could you get me this review by the 20th<add>?</add> <hi rend="underline">if</hi> not, of course do your best.</p>          
                <closer>
                <salute>With love,</salute>
                <signed>Jno.</signed>
                
                <note>JGN:EVN</note>
                </closer>
                
                <postscript><p>I'm rushing with page proofs</p></postscript>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
